<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 31. Gymnopus glabrosipes. Stipe medullary hyphae. Slender generative hyphae among refringent, thick-walled skeletalized hyphae. Standard bar = 10 µm. WTU-F- 9309." , "Figure 30. Gymnopus glabrosipes. Hymenial structures. A Basidium: note 2 sterigmata out of focus B-D Pleurocystidia: note basal clamp connections. Standard bars = 10 µm. WTU-F- 9309." , "Figure 29. Gymnopus glabrosipes. Pileipellis hyphae. A Strongly encrusted hypha with vaguely annular pattern B Hypha with gelatinizing walls and thin slime sheath, with incrusting material on the surface of the slime sheath C Smooth hyphae with gelatinized wall. Standard bars = 10 µm. WTU-F- 9309." , "Figure 28. Gymnopus glabrosipes. Basidiomata and rhizomorphs. Standard bar = 20 mm. WTU-F- 9309." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/115091" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/115090" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/115089" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/115088" .

